Reasoning: The paper proposes a method to automatically generate stylish fashion ensembles by taking into account style information. This involves training a deep neural network to capture style in an automated manner, which suggests the paper falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of an encoder-decoder architecture and attention mechanism also suggests the paper may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves retrieval-based experiments, which suggests it may also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with fashion items, which suggests it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
